# This file is documentation only — nothing reads from a root .env.
# Configure the apps separately:
#   apps/api/.env.example  → apps/api/.env  (loaded by dotenv at server boot)
#   apps/web/.env.example  → apps/web/.env  (loaded by Vite at dev/build time)
#
# At-a-glance list of every variable used across the workspace:
#
# apps/api/.env
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NODE_ENV                       Optional. development | test | production. Default development.
# API_PORT                       Optional. Default 4000.
# WEB_ORIGIN                     Optional. CORS allow-list. Default http://localhost:5173.
# SUPABASE_URL                   Required.
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY              Required.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY      Required. Server-only secret — bypasses RLS.
#
# apps/web/.env
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_APP_NAME                  Optional. Default "Softball Training".
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL              Required.
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY         Required.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL              Optional. Default http://localhost:4000/api.
